SUMMARY:Nothing to do on a Monday? How 'bout Some Great Blues
DESCRIPTION:Portland City Trail Walking Group\nJoin me as we listen to a long time Portland favorite\, Lloyd Jones on the guitar\, a Portland landmark Blues musician accompanied by a variety of top tier musicians making for a great evening. The venue\, the Muddy Rudder Public House on the east side of the Selwood Bridge. It's an intimate venue with great beer and excellent food where you can both hold a conversation and take in some of the best Blues around. It's the Portland thing to do on a Monday evening.\nhttps://muddyrudderpdx.com/music-schedule/
